h3cFlash.name: h3cFlash
h3cFlash.contactinfo: Platform Team Hangzhou H3C Tech. Co., Ltd. Hai-Dian District Beijing P.R. China http://www.h3c.com Zip:100085
h3cFlash.description: This MIB contains objects to manage flash cards and flash card operations. There are no constraints on this MIB.

H3cFlashOperationStatus.name: H3cFlashOperationStatus
H3cFlashOperationStatus.description: The status of the specified operation can be one of the following. opInProgress : The operation is in process. opSuccess : The operation has been completed successfully. opInvalid : The command is invalid or command-protocol-device combination is unsupported by the system. opInvalidProtocol : Invalid protocol is specified. opInvalidSourceName : Invalid source file name is specified. opInvalidDestName : Invalid target name is specified. opInvalidServerAddress : Invalid server address is specified. opDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeviceOpenError : Invalid device name is specified. opDeviceError : Device read, write or erase error. opDeviceNotProgrammable : Device is read-only but a write or erase operation was specified. opDeviceFull : Device is filled to capacity. opFileOpenError : Invalid file name; file not found in partition. opFileTransferError : File transfer was unsuccessful. opFileChecksumError : File checksum in Flash is invalid. opNoMemory : System is running in low on memory. opUnknownFailure : Failure which is unknown. opDeleteFileOpenError : File is in used by another process. opDeleteInvalidDevice : Invalid device name is specified. opDeleteInvalidFunction : Deleted operation is unsupported by the device. opDeleteOperationError : Operation is in a low error. opDeleteInvalidFileName : Invalid file name is specified. pDeleteDeviceBusy : The device is in use and locked by another process. opDeleteParaError : The parameters are invalid. opDeleteInvalidPath : The file path is invalid. opDeleteFileNotExistInSlave : Failed to delete file, because the file is not exist in the slave. opDeleteFileFailedInSlave : Operation is fail when delete file in the slave. opSlaveFull : Operation is fail for the slave don't have enough space. opCopyToSlaveFailure : Operation is fail when copy file to the slave.

H3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.name: H3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode
H3cFlashPartitionUpgradeMode.description: Flash partition upgrade method, i.e., method by which new files can be downloaded into the partition. FLH stands for Flash Load Helper, a feature provided on run-from-Flash systems for upgrading Flash. This feature uses the bootstrap code in ROMs to help in automatic download. This object should be retrieved if the partition status is runFromFlash(2). If the partition status is readOnly(1), the upgrade method would depend on the reason for the readOnly status. For example, it may simply be a matter of installing the programming jumper, or it may require execution of a later version of software that supports the Flash chips. unknown - the current system image does not know how Flash can be programmed. A possible method would be to reload the ROM image and perform the upgrade manually. rxbootFLH - the Flash Load Helper is available to download files to Flash. A copy-to-flash command can be used and this system image will automatically reload the Rxboot image in ROM and direct it to carry out the download request. direct - will be done directly by this image.

H3cFlashPartitionStatus.name: H3cFlashPartitionStatus
H3cFlashPartitionStatus.description: If device is not programmable the value of it will be 'readOnly'; If the current image is running from this partition the value of it will be 'runFromFlash' If device is programmable the value of it will be 'readWrite'.

h3cFlhSupportNum.name: h3cFlhSupportNum
h3cFlhSupportNum.description: Specifies the total number of flash which the system supported. The MIB should not be loaded if there is no flash in the system and so the value here will be a minimum of 1.

h3cFlashTable.name: h3cFlashTable
h3cFlashTable.description: This table gives the properties of all the flashes on the system.

h3cFlhIndex.name: h3cFlhIndex
h3cFlhIndex.description: The index of h3cFlashTable. There are two parts for this index depicted as follows: 31 15 0 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ + entity index + random index + + ( bit 16..31 ) ( bit 0..15 ) + +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++ From bit0 to bit15 (two bytes), it has a minimum value of 1, and maximum value of the same as the value of h3cFlhSupportNum. From bit16 to bit31 (two bytes), it is the physical index the same as the entPhysicalIndex specified in ENTITY-MIB.

h3cFlhSize.name: h3cFlhSize
h3cFlhSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash device indexed by h3cFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device.

h3cFlhPos.name: h3cFlhPos
h3cFlhPos.description: The position of the flash device in system. This object is an index of entPhysicalTable in ENTITY-MIB. If the value of this object is 0, the main processor is indicated.

h3cFlhName.name: h3cFlhName
h3cFlhName.description: The flash name within the system.

h3cFlhChipNum.name: h3cFlhChipNum
h3cFlhChipNum.description: The chip numbers in the flash.

h3cFlhDescr.name: h3cFlhDescr
h3cFlhDescr.description: Description of the purpose of the flash in the system.

h3cFlhInitTime.name: h3cFlhInitTime
h3cFlhInitTime.description: The initialization time for the flash component or partition, recorded using the system time. This will be the boot time for a fixed device. For a removable component or a partition, it will be the initialization time.

h3cFlhRemovable.name: h3cFlhRemovable
h3cFlhRemovable.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be removed or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash device CAN be removed.

h3cFlhPartitionBool.name: h3cFlhPartitionBool
h3cFlhPartitionBool.description: The value indicates whether the flash indexed can be partitioned or not. The true(1) value indicates the flash CAN be partitioned.

h3cFlhMinPartitionSize.name: h3cFlhMinPartitionSize
h3cFlhMinPartitionSize.description: Minimum partition size supported. If h3cFlhDevicePartitionBool is false, the value of this object is the same as h3cFlhSize.

h3cFlhMaxPartitions.name: h3cFlhMaxPartitions
h3cFlhMaxPartitions.description: The maximum count of partitions which the system supports for this flash. If h3cFlhPartitionBool is false, the object value is 1.

h3cFlhPartitionNum.name: h3cFlhPartitionNum
h3cFlhPartitionNum.description: The actual number of partitions supported by the system for this flash. If h3cFlhPartitionBool is false, this value is 1.

h3cFlhKbyteSize.name: h3cFlhKbyteSize
h3cFlhKbyteSize.description: Specifies the total size of the flash device indexed by h3cFlhIndex. The value should be zero if the flash is removed for a removable device.

h3cFlhChipTable.name: h3cFlhChipTable
h3cFlhChipTable.description: Table of properties for all flash chips. Used mainly for diagnostics.

h3cFlhChipID.name: h3cFlhChipID
h3cFlhChipID.description: The manufacturer code (the upper byte) and device code (the lower byte) for a chip. Unknown chip code is presented as 00:00.

h3cFlhChipDescr.name: h3cFlhChipDescr
h3cFlhChipDescr.description: The description of the flash chip.

h3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.name: h3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit
h3cFlhChipWriteTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of write times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

h3cFlhChipWriteTimes.name: h3cFlhChipWriteTimes
h3cFlhChipWriteTimes.description: A count of write times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 25 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after a write operation, and report any errors accordingly.

h3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.name: h3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit
h3cFlhChipEraseTimesLimit.description: The limit for the number of erase times (retries) for a flash chip. If the limit is exceeded an error should be reported by the management station.

h3cFlhChipEraseTimes.name: h3cFlhChipEraseTimes
h3cFlhChipEraseTimes.description: A count of erase times (retries) for the flash chip since initialization. A count of 2000 or more for a single chip indicates a write error. Management stations should note the value of this MIB before and after an erase operation, and report any errors accordingly.

h3cFlhPartitionTable.name: h3cFlhPartitionTable
h3cFlhPartitionTable.description: Properties for the flash partitions. Minimum of one entry in this table.

h3cFlhPartitionEntry.name: h3cFlhPartitionEntry
h3cFlhPartitionEntry.description: An entry of the h3cFlhPartitionTable.Indexed by flash number and partition number.

h3cFlhPartIndex.name: h3cFlhPartIndex
h3cFlhPartIndex.description: An index which specifies a sequenced partition in the system.

h3cFlhPartFirstChip.name: h3cFlhPartFirstChip
h3cFlhPartFirstChip.description: The first chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

h3cFlhPartLastChip.name: h3cFlhPartLastChip
h3cFlhPartLastChip.description: The last chip's sequence number in the partition, by which a chip can be indexed in chip table.

h3cFlhPartSpace.name: h3cFlhPartSpace
h3cFlhPartSpace.description: The total space of the flash partition. The following should be satisfied: h3cFlhPartSpace = n*h3cFlhMinPartitionSize

h3cFlhPartFileNum.name: h3cFlhPartFileNum
h3cFlhPartFileNum.description: The number of all the files in the flash partition.

h3cFlhPartChecksumMethod.name: h3cFlhPartChecksumMethod
h3cFlhPartChecksumMethod.description: The Checksum method which the file system uses.

h3cFlhPartUpgradeMode.name: h3cFlhPartUpgradeMode
h3cFlhPartUpgradeMode.description: The upgrade mode of the Flash partition

h3cFlhPartName.name: h3cFlhPartName
h3cFlhPartName.description: The name of the flash partition given by the system.

h3cFlhPartRequireErase.name: h3cFlhPartRequireErase
h3cFlhPartRequireErase.description: Shows whether a write operation is conditional on partition erase.

h3cFlhPartFileNameLen.name: h3cFlhPartFileNameLen
h3cFlhPartFileNameLen.description: The maximum length of file name supported in the system.

h3cFlhFileEntry.name: h3cFlhFileEntry
h3cFlhFileEntry.description: An entry representing a file. Indexed using flash number, partition number, and file number.

h3cFlhFileIndex.name: h3cFlhFileIndex
h3cFlhFileIndex.description: Index of the table, whose range is from 1 to 2147483647

h3cFlhFileName.name: h3cFlhFileName
h3cFlhFileName.description: A valid file name supported by the file system.

h3cFlhFileSize.name: h3cFlhFileSize
h3cFlhFileSize.description: The file size in bytes excluding the file header of file system. The value should be greater than zero.

h3cFlhFileStatus.name: h3cFlhFileStatus
h3cFlhFileStatus.description: The status should be as follows: deleted(1): The file is in recycle bin. invalidChecksum(2): The checksum of file is invalid; valid(3): A valid file.

h3cFlhFileChecksum.name: h3cFlhFileChecksum
h3cFlhFileChecksum.description: The file checksum in the header of file.

h3cFlhOpEntry.name: h3cFlhOpEntry
h3cFlhOpEntry.description: Note an operation can not be stopped until it is finished. If notification is configured, NMS will receive a notification at the end of the operation. Entries in the table will be removed automatically in 5 minutes. It can also be deleted by NMS directly.

h3cFlhOperIndex.name: h3cFlhOperIndex
h3cFlhOperIndex.description: Specifies the index of an entry. It is a random value when creating an entry.

h3cFlhOperType.name: h3cFlhOperType
h3cFlhOperType.description: Specifies the operation to be executed. net2FlashWithErase Copy a file to flash; erase flash beforehand. net2FlashWithoutErase Copy a file to flash; do not erase flash beforehand. flash2Net Copy a file from flash. delete Delete a file from flash, the file name is specified by h3cFlhOperSourceFile; rename Change a file's name.

h3cFlhOperProtocol.name: h3cFlhOperProtocol
h3cFlhOperProtocol.description: Specifies the protocol used to transfer file. The default protocol is ftp. when 'clusterftp' or 'clustertftp' is selected, the h3cFlhOperServerAddress needn't be set, the server address can be acquired automatically, the value of h3cFlhOperServerAddress is uncertain during operation. Both member switch and commander switch can use them if they support HGMP v2.

h3cFlhOperServerAddress.name: h3cFlhOperServerAddress
h3cFlhOperServerAddress.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation. The default value is 255.255.255.255 This object is replaced by h3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev for it only support IPv4.

h3cFlhOperServerUser.name: h3cFlhOperServerUser
h3cFlhOperServerUser.description: When using ftp to transfer files, the user name must be specified through this node.

h3cFlhOperPassword.name: h3cFlhOperPassword
h3cFlhOperPassword.description: Remote user password for copying via ftp protocol. Optionally, This object may be ignored for protocols other than ftp.

h3cFlhOperSourceFile.name: h3cFlhOperSourceFile
h3cFlhOperSourceFile.description: Specifies the source file name to be transferred. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. It must be specified.

h3cFlhOperDestinationFile.name: h3cFlhOperDestinationFile
h3cFlhOperDestinationFile.description: Specifies the destination file name. It may be located on flash or remote server. It may include the file path if it is applicable. If it is not specified, the destination file name is the same as source file name for application.

h3cFlhOperEndNotification.name: h3cFlhOperEndNotification
h3cFlhOperEndNotification.description: If the value of it is specified 'true', a notification will be generated at the end of the operation. Else no notification will be generated.

h3cFlhOperProgress.name: h3cFlhOperProgress
h3cFlhOperProgress.description: The progress described as the time taken for the operation.

h3cFlhOperRowStatus.name: h3cFlhOperRowStatus
h3cFlhOperRowStatus.description: The row status of this table entry.

h3cFlhOperServerPort.name: h3cFlhOperServerPort
h3cFlhOperServerPort.description: The port of remote host acting as server for operation. If the value of this object is not specified, the server port is the known protocol port.

h3cFlhOperSrvAddrType.name: h3cFlhOperSrvAddrType
h3cFlhOperSrvAddrType.description: The type of IP address for h3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.

h3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.name: h3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev
h3cFlhOperSrvAddrRev.description: The address of remote host acting as server for operation.

h3cFlhOperSrvVPNName.name: h3cFlhOperSrvVPNName
h3cFlhOperSrvVPNName.description: The VPN instance of this operation uses.

h3cFlhOperNotification.name: h3cFlhOperNotification
h3cFlhOperNotification.description: A h3cFlhOperNotification is sent at the completion of a flash copy operation if h3cFlhOperEndNotification is true.

h3cFlhMIBCompliance.name: h3cFlhMIBCompliance
h3cFlhMIBCompliance.description: The statement of compliance for those implementing this MIB.

h3cFlhGroup.name: h3cFlhGroup
h3cFlhGroup.description: A collection of objects on Flash level information.

h3cFlhChipGroup.name: h3cFlhChipGroup
h3cFlhChipGroup.description: A collection of objects on chip level information.

h3cFlhPartitionGroup.name: h3cFlhPartitionGroup
h3cFlhPartitionGroup.description: A collection of objects providing on partition level information.

h3cFlhFileGroup.name: h3cFlhFileGroup
h3cFlhFileGroup.description: A collection of objects on file level information.

h3cFlhOperationGroup.name: h3cFlhOperationGroup
h3cFlhOperationGroup.description: A collection of objects of flash operations.

h3cFlhNotificationGroup.name: h3cFlhNotificationGroup
h3cFlhNotificationGroup.description: The collection of notifications in the module
